description:
&lt;p&gt;** 14 month Fixed Term Contract - Apprenticeship **&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome applications from individuals wishing to become an Apprentice and gain experience in the NHS. You will develop new skills and knowledge whilst working with an established team gaining valuable work experience and a recognised apprenticeship qualification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be enrolled with a local education provider and will be required to complete your Level 2 Customer Service Practitioner Apprenticeship Programme within the duration of the placement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Respiratory Medicine Department is a busy and interesting work environment. We provide many services including sleep, asthma, interstitial lung disease, cystic fibrosis and tuberculosis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a Receptionist to join our busy Respiratory Reception Team. As a post holder, your key responsibilities will include managing a busy reception desk, dealing with telephone enquiries and preparing notes for clinic, making appointments and providing general administrative support to the clinical team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will provide a high quality reception and support service within the Respiratory Medicine Outpatients Department, and as such, will need to be able to communicate well with patients and their relatives, the general public and a wide range of multi-professional staff, internal and external to the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will liaise with staff in other departments, community services and General Practitioners. Welcome patients, relatives and visitors to the department in a friendly manner. You will ensure that a high standard of service to the patient is maintained.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To support the delivery of a high quality, safe and compassionate healthcare service, all staff are expected to act as a role model to others in all aspects of their work and consistently demonstrate NNUH’s ‘PRIDE’ values of People focused, Respect, Dedication, Integrity and Excellence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Various weekdays, some weekend cover may be required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Eligibility Criteria:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;All applicants must be:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Aged 16+&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resident in the UK/EEA for the last three years&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must not have a Degree, Level 4 qualification or above&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must NOT be in any form of formal government-funded education&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications and Skills Required:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good general standard of education&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4 GCSE’s at Grade D/3 or above (or equivalent)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good standard of literacy and numeracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good communication and interpersonal skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good IT skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The NNUH are pleased to be able to offer a variety of challenging apprenticeships. Should you be selected for interview we may wish to discuss with you a range of alternative positions for you to consider.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full time:&lt;/strong&gt; 37.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date:&lt;/strong&gt; 24th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Open for applications:&lt;/strong&gt; 28th October 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Close for applications:&lt;/strong&gt; 8th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nicole Sellars - Deputy Administration Manager&lt;/p&gt;
